OL,7,Foffences given his previous offending
OL,8,Fwhich incudes breaching court orders
OL,9,Fas well as the manslaughter
OL,10,Fconviction, the officer said an
OL,11,Fadditional objection was that Griffin
OL,12,F"fled the scene and went to ground for
OL,13,Ffour days before he was arrested and
OL,14,Fwas actively evading police."
OL,16,FWhile he conceded Griffin's previous
OL,17,Foffending, defence solicitor Clive
OL,18,FFullerton highlighted the defendant
OL,19,Fhad killed the man "when he was
OL,20,F15...and that was an incident where he
OL,21,Fwas defending his mother."
